snippet.textDisplay: Phool Banro in the last season and now this! It's incredible to see Coke Studio Pak bringing this wonderful fusion of Rajasthani folk and contemporary music in such a beautiful way! Again the strings section in between sounds very refreshing. Overall I find strings have been very intelligently and creatively used in songs this season. No wonder the producers go by the same name! :)

snippet.textDisplay:
I am following Coke Studio Pakistan from the very first episode and all those years I have quiet improved my musical vocabulary but from season 7 I feel that they are putting "too much" in one track which can kill the beauty sometimes.....I can feel the influence of Bollywood in CS Pak and the element of "Saadgi" diminishing away...and I think many people from across the border might agree with me....I am not giving a Cry for Rohail Hyatt to come back I just want it to be like the way it was before....

As for this track.....Mulazim nailed it!
